<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12154h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12154h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12154h"> 154(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> S. Patercius / civium</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It was only shortly before his death that Celestine gave this mission <font color="green">[the conversion of Ireland]</font> to Ireland&apos;s apostle and on that occasion bestowed on him many relics and other spiritual gifts, and gave him the name &ldquo;Patercius&rdquo; or &ldquo;Patritius&rdquo;, not as an honorary title, but as a foreshadowing of the fruitfulness and merit of his apostolate whereby he became <i>pater civium</i> (the father of his people). <small> <a name="CEPEL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CEPEL"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Pelagius&rdquo;</cite></a> <cite a>Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) [Patrtick] 554b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
